\begin_layout Standard
Este teorema nos permite construir polinomios de forma recursiva, ya que
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
P_{0}\!\left(x\right) & =f\!\left[x_{0}\right]=f\!\left(x_{0}\right)\\
P_{1}\!\left(x\right) & =f\!\left[x_{0}\right]+f\!\left[x_{0},x_{1}\right]\cdot\left(x-x_{0}\right)\\
P_{2}\!\left(x\right) & =f\!\left[x_{0}\right]+f\!\left[x_{0},x_{1}\right]\cdot\left(x-x_{0}\right)+f\!\left[x_{0},x_{1},x_{2}\right]\cdot\left(x-x_{0}\right)\cdot\left(x-x_{1}\right)\\
 & \vdots\\
P_{n}\!\left(x\right) & =f\!\left[x_{0}\right]+\sum_{k=1}^{n}f\!\left[x_{0},\dots,x_{k}\right]\cdot\prod_{i=0}^{k-1}\left(x-x_{i}\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

