\begin_layout Solution*
Para la cota, tomamos 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{a}=\min\!\left\{ x_{0},\dots,x_{n}\right\} $
\end_inset

 y 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{b}=\max\!\left\{ x_{0},\dots,x_{n}\right\} $
\end_inset

 y utilizamos que
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left|f\!\left(x\right)-P_{n}\!\left(x\right)\right|\le\frac{\max\!\left\{ \left|f^{\left.n+1\right)}\!\left(x\right)\right|:x\in\left[x_{a},x_{b}\right]\right\} }{\left(n+1\right)!}\cdot\left|\left(x-x_{0}\right)\cdots\left(x-x_{n}\right)\right|
\]

\end_inset

y en particular, para 
\begin_inset Formula $f\!\left(x\right)=\sin\!\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

, tenemos que la derivada 
\begin_inset Formula $n+1$
\end_inset

-ésima en este caso es su derivada cuarta, es decir, 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{\left.4\right)}\!\left(x\right)=\sin\!\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Por tanto
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\max\left\{ \left|f^{\left.4\right)}\!\left(x\right)\right|:x\in\left\{ 0,\frac{1}{4}\pi,\frac{3}{4}\pi,\pi\right\} \right\} =\left|\sin\!\left(\frac{1}{4}\pi\right)\right|=\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}
