\end_inset

 y sea 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{2}:\left[a,b\right]\to\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 el polinomio de grado menor o igual que dos que interpola a 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 respecto a los nodos 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{a+b}{2}$
\end_inset

 y 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

.
 Sea 
\begin_inset Formula $h=\frac{b-a}{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Entonces existe cierto 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\in\left[a,b\right]$
\end_inset

 tal que 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int_{a}^{b}f\!\left(x\right)\,\text{d}x-\int_{a}^{b}P_{2}\!\left(x\right)\,\text{d}x=-\frac{f^{\left.iv\right)}\!\left(\theta\right)}{90}h^{5}
\]

